        "Finally, instead of relying on an arbitrary snapshot date, we dynamically anchor our REFERENCE_DATE to the latest valid transaction in the dataset.\n",
        "\n",
        "INTERPRETATION:\n",
        "This step protects the mathematical integrity of the customer lifecycle. By purging these records, we prevent \"Data Poisoning\"—a situation where a model incorrectly learns from impossible patterns. Without this, features like \"Days since last purchase\" would produce negative values, which would severely confuse the predictive algorithms.\n",
        "\n",
        "KEY FINDING:\n",
        "Timeline errors affect roughly 6% of the raw data. While the dataset is rich, the logic identified 121 corrupted rows. Removing these results in a \"Gold Standard\" baseline of 1,879 high-integrity records, ensuring all future RFM calculations and predictive modeling are grounded in reality."
